solution.p:
Setting s(t) = 0 and applying the quadratic formula with a=-16,
b=41, c=37:

  t &= \frac{-41 \pm \sqrt{41^2 - 4(-16)(37)}}{2(-16)}
  &= \frac{-41 \pm \sqrt{1681 + 2368}}{-32}
  &= \frac{-41 \pm \sqrt{4049}}{-32}.

Taking the root that gives t > 0: t = \frac{-41 - \sqrt{4049}}{-32} \approx 3.27 seconds.

The vertex occurs at t = -\frac{b}{2a} = -\frac{41}{2(-16)} = \frac{41}{32} \approx 1.28 seconds.
The maximum height is
s\!\left(\frac{41}{32}\right) = -16 \cdot \frac{1681}{1024} + 41 \cdot \frac{41}{32} + 37 = \frac{4049}{64} \approx 63.3 \text{ feet.}
